Abendroth, Hermann - Signed Photo Postcard
(Item #: M2379-X4-2)
German conductor (1883-1956), director of the Cologne Conservatory, Lower Rhenish Music Festival, regularly conducted the London Symphony Orchestra, later the Berlin Radio Symphony Orchestra (after being banned in West Germany for his nazi affiliations during WWII).
Signed photo, 4 x 5.75 inches, stamped on verso by photographer Harry Evers, Weimar, in excellent condition.
Also included is an unsigned photo postcard by Weirich from Bayreuth Festival (see scans).
